The paper deals with deep learning methods for hyperspectral image classification, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of nonlinear manifolds and hierarchical clustering, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method also involves preserving geodesic distances, which is a concept related to neural networks (cs.NE) and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
